definition[0]: a container with food for animals or birds
definition[1]: something that provides supplies for something else
example[1]: The Shyok River is a major feeder of the Indus River.
example[2]: The length of the feeder pipe is 50m.
definition[2]: a piece of equipment that supplies something to a machine
definition[3]: a person or animal that eats in a particular way
example[4]: Catfish are bottom feeders (=they feed at the bottom of rivers).
definition[4]: a small road, railway line, or airline service that takes traffic to a main road, line, or service
